ed, and suggests that the effective ionization parameter in AGN may be a\ndecreasing function of luminosity. We are also able to constrain, subject to\nour assumption that gravity dominates the motions of the BLR gas, the scaling\nrelationship between the mass of the central black holes and the luminosity in\nAGN: M \\propto L^{0.5+-0.1}. This is inconsistent with all AGN having optical\nluminosity that is a constant fraction of the Eddington luminosity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 25 Nov 1999 20:33:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 17 Dec 1999 16:35:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-10-31"}
